			<img id="band" alt="band photo" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Paul_Revere_and_the_Raiders_1967.JPG/220px-Paul_Revere_and_the_Raiders_1967.JPG" />
		
			<div id="info">
				If you can look past the silly outfits, the cheesy comedy and the goofy on-stage antics, you'll see that 
				for brief time in the mid-sixties one particular line-up of Paul Revere & The Raiders was possibly the
				best American rock band of the age.  Combining garage-rock aesthetics and psychedelic-rock style the 
				band melded a musical image that meshed perfectly with the vocal style of singer Mark Lindsay and the
				songs, written by both band members and outside songwriters, to push the band to the top of the charts.
		
			</div>

